%N A398015 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} mu(k)^2 * log(k) / k^2, where mu is the Möbius function.
%H A398015 Matthew Perkins and Robert A. Van Gorder, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11139-018-0037-4">Closed-form calculation of infinite products of Glaisher-type related to Dirichlet series</a>, The Ramanujan Journal, Vol. 49, No. 2 (2019), pp. 371-389. See p. 381, Corollary 2.9.
%F A398015 Equals Sum_{k>=1, k squarefree} log(k) / k^2.
%F A398015 Equals (15/Pi^2) * (gamma + log(2*Pi) - 12*zeta'(-1) - 8/3 - 240*zeta'(-3)), where gamma is Euler's constant (A001620).
%F A398015 Equals (15/Pi^2) * (gamma + log(2*Pi) + 12*log(A) + 240*log(A_3), A is the Glaisher-Kinkelin constant (A074962), and A_3 is the third Bendersky constant (A243263).
%e A398015 0.672703958329276343252616048580694983842942621553988...
%t A398015 RealDigits[(15/Pi^2)*(Log[2*Pi] + EulerGamma - 12*Zeta'[-1] - 8/3 - 240*Zeta'[-3]), 10, 120][[1]]
%o A398015 (PARI) (15/Pi^2) * (log(2*Pi) + Euler - 12*zeta'(-1) - 8/3 - 240*zeta'(-3))
